lgp.core.evolution.training

Class TrainingJob<TProgram,TMessage extends TrainingUpdateMessage>

  • lgp.core.evolution.training.TrainingJob<TProgram,TMessage>
  • Type Parameters:
    TProgram - The type of program being evolved.
    TMessage -
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DistributedTrainingJob, SequentialTrainingJob

    public class TrainingJob<TProgram,TMessage extends TrainingUpdateMessage>

    Represents an asynchronous training operation.

    As different class Trainer implementations will have different requirements, it is up to the implementor to define how the job should handle various requests.

    class Trainer

      • subscribeToUpdates

        public void subscribeToUpdates(kotlin.jvm.functions.Function1<? super TMessage,kotlin.Unit> callback)

        Subscribes a callback function that will be executed each time a interface TrainingUpdateMessage is received.

        The callback will be passed the message and allow the subscriber to use the value as it wishes.

        Note: If the class Trainer implementation does not provide a communication channel then this function can be left as not implemented.

        Parameters:
        callback - The function to execute when a interface TrainingUpdateMessage is received.
        See Also:
        interface TrainingUpdateMessage, class Trainer
